abstract: Anita Hill reflected on the 1991 Clarence Thomas hearings and the role former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. played in them.
snippet: Anita Hill reflected on the 1991 Clarence Thomas hearings and the role former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. played in them.
lead_paragraph: Anita Hill spoke by phone this week with The New York Times, reflecting on the Clarence Thomas hearings in 1991 that put a spotlight on sexual harassment and treatment of accusers.

headline_main: Excerpts From Anita Hill’s Interview With The Times

abstract: Susan Bro, whose daughter was killed at a white supremacist rally in Charlottesville, Va., said she warned Mr. Biden to tread carefully around the episode and spoke with him about grief.
snippet: Susan Bro, whose daughter was killed at a white supremacist rally in Charlottesville, Va., said she warned Mr. Biden to tread carefully around the episode and spoke with him about grief.
lead_paragraph: Around 7:20 a.m. on Thursday, Susan Bro began getting text messages. Was she all right? How did she feel about what Joe Biden had done?

headline_main: Joe Biden Reaches Out to Anita Hill
headline_print_headline: Joe Biden Reaches Out to Anita Hill

abstract: Mr. Biden raised more in his first 24 hours than any other candidate, easing concerns among some supporters over his ability to raise money.
snippet: Mr. Biden raised more in his first 24 hours than any other candidate, easing concerns among some supporters over his ability to raise money.
lead_paragraph: Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s presidential campaign announced Friday that it had raised $6.3 million in its opening 24 hours, surpassing the first-day totals of his rivals and easing concerns among some supporters over whether he would be able to compete financially in the Democratic primary.

abstract: Mr. Biden responded to criticism over his handling of Anita Hill’s 1991 testimony. Here are our observations from the show.
snippet: Mr. Biden responded to criticism over his handling of Anita Hill’s 1991 testimony. Here are our observations from the show.
lead_paragraph: Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. sat down with “The View” for his first extended interview since announcing his third run for president on Thursday. The show, hosted by an all-female panel, was an interesting choice of venue for the 76-year-old Democrat: Mr. Biden entered the race weeks after several women came forward to say his interactions with them had made them uncomfortable, and he is facing a fresh round of criticism for his treatment of Anita Hill during the 1991 confirmation hearings of Justice Clarence Thomas.

abstract: Mr. Biden, appearing on “The View,” offered remorse but not a straightforward apology about a controversy that has shadowed the start of his campaign.
snippet: Mr. Biden, appearing on “The View,” offered remorse but not a straightforward apology about a controversy that has shadowed the start of his campaign.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Joseph R. Biden Jr. on Friday repeatedly declined to directly apologize to Anita Hill for his handling of the 1991 Clarence Thomas hearings, using his first interview as a presidential candidate to offer a broad statement of remorse for how she was treated but refusing to demonstrate contrition about a controversy that has shadowed the start of his campaign.
